# DynaCharting Manifest DSL — Design

## 0. Ground truth this is built on

- **Raw feed is long-format events.** Confirmed in `apps/showcase/data/market/AAPL.json`: `{ "t":0, "streamKey":"AAPL", "field":"lastPrice", "value":187.61 }`, plus `field:"depth.bid.0.size"`, `field:"volume"`, `field:"open"`, `field:"close"` etc. This is the *only* substrate the manifest may assume: a stream of `(t, streamKey, field, value)` scalars. NOT geometry, NOT instructions.
- **The engine is a pure renderer.** `core/src/pipelines/PipelineCatalog.cpp` registers 10 pipelines; `core/src/commands/CommandProcessor.cpp` (validateDrawItem, ~L570) hard-rejects geometry whose format ≠ the pipeline's required vertex format. `core/src/ingest/IngestProcessor.cpp` fills anonymous `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffers via a 13-byte-header binary record. The only transform is a baked `mat3` (`core/include/dc/scene/Types.hpp` recomputeMat3).
- **The negative space, measured.** `apps/showcase/views/treemap/manifest.ts` is the proof: 188 lines (buildSectors → squarify → perfColor → clip-space tessellation) just to emit `pos2_color4` triangles, because the engine has no DATASET / SCALE / TRANSFORM / ENCODING layer. The manifest below is exactly the artifact that replaces those 188 lines with a declarative spec the engine executes per frame.

The manifest is a **typed streaming dataflow DAG**: `dataSources → transforms → scales → marks(encodings) → coords → layers`, all nodes addressed by string id in one namespace. The engine compiles it once into (a) a transform schedule (per streaming-class), (b) scale objects with auto-domains, and (c) DrawItem/buffer/geometry bindings into the existing scene graph; then runs it every frame off the live tables.

---

## 1. Top-level schema sketch

```jsonc
{
  "version": "dc-manifest/1",
  "id": "candles-sma",                 // stable id; namespaces emitted scene-graph ids

  // ── DATA PLANE: how raw (t,streamKey,field,value) events fill named typed columns
  "data": {
    "sources": [
      {
        "id": "ticks",                 // dataset id (referenced as "ticks")
        "kind": "stream",              // stream | static | derived
        "stream": {
          // selector over the raw feed; matched events route into this table
          "match": { "streamKey": ["AAPL"], "field": ["open","high","low","close","volume"] },
          // long->wide PIVOT: one row per `key`, columns named by `field`
          "rowKey": "t",               // events sharing this become one row
          "columns": {                 // NAMED, TYPED columns — the missing data model
            "t":      { "from": "rowKey", "dtype": "f64", "role": "time" },
            "open":   { "from": "field:open",   "dtype": "f32" },
            "high":   { "from": "field:high",   "dtype": "f32" },
            "low":    { "from": "field:low",    "dtype": "f32" },
            "close":  { "from": "field:close",  "dtype": "f32" },
            "volume": { "from": "field:volume", "dtype": "f32" }
          }
        },
        "retention": { "policy": "keepLast", "rows": 5000 }   // ring-buffer cap (D6.1)
      }
    ]
  },

  // ── TRANSFORM PIPELINE: named ops, each consumes an upstream output, emits a new dataset
  "transforms": [
    {
      "id": "sma20", "in": "ticks", "op": "window",
      "window": { "field": "close", "frame": [-19, 0], "agg": "mean", "as": "sma20" },
      "stream": { "class": "incremental", "cadence": "perFrame" }   // O(Δ) per append
    }
    // op ∈ filter|formula|bin|aggregate|stack|sort|window|kde|histogram|
    //       fft|treemap|force|contour|voronoi|geoproject|customCompute
  ],

  // ── SCALES: column domain -> visual range. Replaces the baked affine.
  "scales": [
    { "id": "xt", "type": "time",   "domainFrom": { "data": "ticks", "field": "t" },
      "range": "width",  "autodomain": { "mode": "data", "stream": "extend" } },
    { "id": "yp", "type": "linear", "domainFrom": { "data": "ticks", "fields": ["low","high"] },
      "range": "height", "nice": true, "autodomain": { "mode": "data", "stream": "extend", "pad": 0.05 } },
    { "id": "vol","type": "log",    "domainFrom": { "data": "ticks", "field": "volume" }, "range": "height" }
    // type ∈ linear|log|pow|sqrt|symlog|time|utc|ordinal|band|point|
    //        quantile|quantize|threshold|sequential|diverging
  ],

  // ── COORDS: the coordinate system marks resolve channels into (GPU divergence #4)
  "coords": { "type": "cartesian" },   // cartesian | polar{theta,radius} | geo{projection} | affineFree

  // ── MARKS: each binds to a target pipeline; channels reference scale(field)
  "marks": [
    {
      "id": "candles", "type": "rect", "from": "ticks",
      "pipeline": "instancedCandle@1",            // explicit GPU target (divergence #2)
      "encoding": {
        "x":     { "scale": "xt", "field": "t" },
        "yOpen": { "scale": "yp", "field": "open" },
        "yClose":{ "scale": "yp", "field": "close" },
        "yHigh": { "scale": "yp", "field": "high" },
        "yLow":  { "scale": "yp", "field": "low" },
        "color": { "condition": { "test": "close >= open", "value": "#26a69a" }, "value": "#ef5350" }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "smaLine", "type": "line", "from": "sma20",
      "pipeline": "lineAA@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x": { "scale": "xt", "field": "t" },
        "y": { "scale": "yp", "field": "sma20" },
        "color": { "value": "#ffb300" }, "strokeWidth": { "value": 1.5 }
      }
    }
  ],

  // ── FACET / SMALL MULTIPLES (optional): replicate marks across a partition column
  "facet": null,   // { "field":"streamKey", "columns":2 } -> one pane per value

  // ── LAYERING / COMPOSITION: pane regions + draw order
  "layers": [ { "id": "main", "region": { "x":[0,1], "y":[0,1] }, "marks": ["candles","smaLine"] } ],

  // ── INTERACTION: pan/zoom drives scale domains (NOT a baked transform)
  "interaction": {
    "panZoom": { "x": { "scale": "xt", "mode": "translateScale" },
                 "y": { "scale": "yp", "mode": "translateScale" } },
    "follow":  { "scale": "xt", "mode": "stickRight" }   // streaming auto-scroll
  }
}
```

### Field-level typing rules (the anti-nonsense contract — §3)

| Concept | Reference syntax | Validation |
|---|---|---|
| dataset | `"from": "ticks"` on a mark / `"in": "ticks"` on a transform | id must exist in `data.sources` ∪ `transforms[].id` |
| column | `"field": "close"` | must exist in the referenced dataset's column set (computed from source columns + transform `as` outputs) and have a dtype the channel/scale accepts |
| scale | `"scale": "yp"` | id must exist in `scales`; its `domainFrom` dtype must be compatible with its `type` (e.g. `band` needs ordinal/string, `log` needs positive quantitative) |
| transform output | transform N may name dataset M only if M is declared earlier (DAG, acyclic) | topological sort must succeed; no forward refs, no cycles |
| pipeline/format | `"pipeline": "instancedCandle@1"` + mark type | mark type must be in the pipeline's allowed mark set; channel set must cover the pipeline's required vertex/instance fields |

---

## 2. Three full worked examples (entirely from raw data)

### 2.1 Candlestick + SMA(20) — financial

Raw feed in: `{t, streamKey:"AAPL", field ∈ {open,high,low,close,volume}, value}`. No precompute; the engine pivots to OHLC rows, runs a streaming window mean, auto-domains both axes, and binds two marks.

```json
{
  "version": "dc-manifest/1",
  "id": "candles-sma",
  "data": {
    "sources": [{
      "id": "ohlc", "kind": "stream",
      "stream": {
        "match": { "streamKey": ["AAPL"], "field": ["open","high","low","close","volume"] },
        "rowKey": "t",
        "columns": {
          "t":      { "from": "rowKey",       "dtype": "f64", "role": "time" },
          "open":   { "from": "field:open",   "dtype": "f32" },
          "high":   { "from": "field:high",   "dtype": "f32" },
          "low":    { "from": "field:low",    "dtype": "f32" },
          "close":  { "from": "field:close",  "dtype": "f32" },
          "volume": { "from": "field:volume", "dtype": "f32" }
        }
      },
      "retention": { "policy": "keepLast", "rows": 5000 }
    }]
  },
  "transforms": [
    { "id": "withSma", "in": "ohlc", "op": "window",
      "window": { "field": "close", "frame": [-19, 0], "agg": "mean", "as": "sma20", "minPeriods": 1 },
      "stream": { "class": "incremental", "cadence": "perFrame" } }
  ],
  "scales": [
    { "id": "xt", "type": "time",   "domainFrom": { "data": "ohlc", "field": "t" },
      "range": "width",  "autodomain": { "mode": "data", "stream": "extend" } },
    { "id": "yp", "type": "linear", "domainFrom": { "data": "ohlc", "fields": ["low","high"] },
      "range": "height", "nice": true,
      "autodomain": { "mode": "data", "stream": "extend", "pad": 0.05 } }
  ],
  "coords": { "type": "cartesian" },
  "marks": [
    { "id": "candles", "type": "rect", "from": "withSma", "pipeline": "instancedCandle@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x":      { "scale": "xt", "field": "t" },
        "yOpen":  { "scale": "yp", "field": "open" },
        "yClose": { "scale": "yp", "field": "close" },
        "yHigh":  { "scale": "yp", "field": "high" },
        "yLow":   { "scale": "yp", "field": "low" },
        "width":  { "value": 0.7, "unit": "bandFraction" },
        "color":  { "condition": { "test": "close >= open", "value": "#26a69a" },
                    "value": "#ef5350" }
      } },
    { "id": "smaLine", "type": "line", "from": "withSma", "pipeline": "lineAA@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x": { "scale": "xt", "field": "t" },
        "y": { "scale": "yp", "field": "sma20" },
        "color": { "value": "#ffb300" }, "strokeWidth": { "value": 1.5 }
      } }
  ],
  "layers": [ { "id": "main", "region": { "x": [0,1], "y": [0,1] }, "marks": ["candles", "smaLine"] } ],
  "interaction": {
    "panZoom": { "x": { "scale": "xt", "mode": "translateScale" }, "y": { "scale": "yp", "mode": "translateScale" } },
    "follow":  { "scale": "xt", "mode": "stickRight" }
  }
}
```

What the engine does per frame: append-pivot new events into `ohlc` (O(Δ)); extend `sma20` window mean for new rows only (incremental); update `xt`/`yp` running min/max (class-1); for each visible row pack an `instancedCandle@1` instance (`Candle6`, 24B) and an `lineAA@1` vertex; upload dirty ranges via `CpuBufferStore`. Every transform here is class-1 incremental — this is the 60–120 Hz happy path.

### 2.2 Treemap — replaces the 188-line `treemap/manifest.ts` precompute

Raw feed in: same OHLC events for AAPL/MSFT/NVDA/TSLA. The `treemap` transform is a **named heavyweight layout primitive** (CHART-UNIVERSE primitive #2: constrained recursive space-filling) that the engine owns — squarified Bruls/Huizing/van Wijk, run on-update, emitting one row per leaf with `{x0,y0,x1,y1}` rect columns. A per-instance-color rect mark (the KIND-1 mark gap from VIEWS-DECOMP) then draws all tiles in one DrawItem.

```json
{
  "version": "dc-manifest/1",
  "id": "treemap-market",
  "data": {
    "sources": [{
      "id": "bars", "kind": "stream",
      "stream": {
        "match": { "streamKey": ["AAPL","MSFT","NVDA","TSLA"], "field": ["open","close","volume"] },
        "rowKey": "t",
        "groupKey": "streamKey",
        "columns": {
          "symbol": { "from": "field:streamKey", "dtype": "str", "role": "group" },
          "t":      { "from": "rowKey",          "dtype": "f64", "role": "time" },
          "open":   { "from": "field:open",      "dtype": "f32" },
          "close":  { "from": "field:close",     "dtype": "f32" },
          "volume": { "from": "field:volume",    "dtype": "f32" }
        }
      },
      "retention": { "policy": "keepLast", "rows": 40, "per": "symbol" }
    }]
  },
  "transforms": [
    { "id": "byBucket", "in": "bars", "op": "bin",
      "bin": { "field": "t", "maxbins": 5, "as": "bucket" },
      "stream": { "class": "incremental", "cadence": "perFrame" } },
    { "id": "leaves", "in": "byBucket", "op": "aggregate",
      "aggregate": { "groupBy": ["symbol", "bucket"],
        "ops": [ { "field": "volume", "agg": "sum",   "as": "size" },
                 { "field": "open",   "agg": "first", "as": "o" },
                 { "field": "close",  "agg": "last",  "as": "c" } ] },
      "formula": [ { "expr": "(c - o) / o", "as": "perf" } ],
      "stream": { "class": "windowed", "cadence": "onHop" } },
    { "id": "tiles", "in": "leaves", "op": "treemap",
      "treemap": {
        "hierarchy": ["symbol", "bucket"],   // 2-level nesting (sector -> leaf)
        "size": "size", "method": "squarify", "padding": 0.006, "tile": "stable",
        "as": { "x0":"x0", "y0":"y0", "x1":"x1", "y1":"y1" }
      },
      "stream": { "class": "globalRecompute", "cadence": { "debounceMs": 100, "trigger": "onUpdate" } } }
  ],
  "scales": [
    { "id": "px", "type": "linear", "domain": [0,1], "range": "width" },
    { "id": "py", "type": "linear", "domain": [0,1], "range": "height" },
    { "id": "heat", "type": "diverging", "domainFrom": { "data": "tiles", "field": "perf" },
      "domainMid": 0, "range": ["#ef5350", "#3a3f4b", "#26a69a"],
      "autodomain": { "mode": "symmetric", "stream": "extend" } }
  ],
  "coords": { "type": "cartesian" },
  "marks": [
    { "id": "cells", "type": "rect", "from": "tiles", "pipeline": "triGradient@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x":  { "scale": "px", "field": "x0" },
        "x2": { "scale": "px", "field": "x1" },
        "y":  { "scale": "py", "field": "y0" },
        "y2": { "scale": "py", "field": "y1" },
        "color": { "scale": "heat", "field": "perf" }     // per-instance color via scale
      } },
    { "id": "labels", "type": "text", "from": "tiles", "pipeline": "textSDF@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x": { "scale": "px", "field": "x0", "offset": 4 },
        "y": { "scale": "py", "field": "y0", "offset": 12 },
        "text": { "field": "symbol" }, "size": { "value": 11 }
      } }
  ],
  "layers": [ { "id": "main", "region": { "x":[0,1], "y":[0,1] }, "marks": ["cells","labels"] } ],
  "interaction": { "panZoom": { "enabled": false } }
}
```

The 188-line hand-tessellation collapses to: `bin → aggregate+formula → treemap` transforms + a per-instance-color `rect` mark + a `text` mark. The squarified math lives **in the engine** as the `treemap` op, scheduled on a 100 ms debounce (STREAMING class-3) rather than recomputed every data tick. Note `tile:"stable"` mirrors the existing manifest's no-sort stable-identity choice so a tile's color slot is continuous frame-to-frame.

### 2.3 Node-link force graph — the iterative/stateful tail (escape-hatch territory)

Raw feed in: two event flavors — node mass events `{field:"node.<id>.weight"}` and edge events `{field:"edge.<src>-<dst>.weight"}`. The `force` transform is CHART-UNIVERSE primitive #1 (iterative fixed-point layout): the engine owns simulation state (positions persist across frames), which a stateless manifest cannot express — so it is a **named stateful transform** with declared parameters, and its inner physics is the optional `customCompute` escape hatch (divergence #5).

```json
{
  "version": "dc-manifest/1",
  "id": "force-network",
  "data": {
    "sources": [
      { "id": "nodes", "kind": "stream",
        "stream": {
          "match": { "field:glob": "node.*.weight" },
          "rowKey": "field:capture(node.(?<id>[^.]+).weight, id)",
          "columns": {
            "id":     { "from": "rowKey",        "dtype": "str", "role": "key" },
            "weight": { "from": "field:value",   "dtype": "f32" }
          } } },
      { "id": "edges", "kind": "stream",
        "stream": {
          "match": { "field:glob": "edge.*.weight" },
          "rowKey": "field:capture(edge.(?<src>[^-]+)-(?<dst>[^.]+).weight, src, dst)",
          "columns": {
            "src":    { "from": "capture:src", "dtype": "str", "ref": { "data": "nodes", "field": "id" } },
            "dst":    { "from": "capture:dst", "dtype": "str", "ref": { "data": "nodes", "field": "id" } },
            "weight": { "from": "field:value", "dtype": "f32" }
          } } }
    ]
  },
  "transforms": [
    { "id": "sim", "in": "nodes", "op": "force",
      "force": {
        "nodes": "nodes", "edges": "edges",
        "nodeId": "id", "edgeSrc": "src", "edgeDst": "dst",
        "forces": [
          { "type": "manyBody",  "strength": -30 },
          { "type": "link",      "distance": 30, "strengthField": "weight" },
          { "type": "center",    "x": 0, "y": 0 },
          { "type": "collide",   "radiusField": "weight", "radiusScale": "rNode" }
        ],
        "alpha": { "start": 1.0, "decay": 0.02, "min": 0.001, "reheatOnInsert": 0.3 },
        "as": { "x": "fx", "y": "fy" }            // engine-owned persistent positions
      },
      "stream": { "class": "iterative", "cadence": "perFrame", "state": "persistent" },
      "compute": {                                 // ESCAPE HATCH (optional; default = built-in N-body)
        "backend": "wgsl",
        "passes": [ { "entry": "integrate", "dispatch": { "x": "ceil(nodeCount/64)" } } ],
        "io": { "read": ["nodes.weight","edges.src","edges.dst","edges.weight"],
                "readWrite": ["sim.fx","sim.fy","sim.vx","sim.vy"] },
        "wgsl": "@group(0)@binding(0) var<storage,read_write> pos: array<vec2<f32>>; /* ...verlet integrate... */ @compute @workgroup_size(64) fn integrate(){ /* repulsion+spring+center, write pos */ }"
      } }
  ],
  "scales": [
    { "id": "gx", "type": "linear", "domainFrom": { "data": "sim", "field": "fx" }, "range": "width",
      "autodomain": { "mode": "data", "stream": "extend", "pad": 0.1 } },
    { "id": "gy", "type": "linear", "domainFrom": { "data": "sim", "field": "fy" }, "range": "height",
      "autodomain": { "mode": "data", "stream": "extend", "pad": 0.1 } },
    { "id": "rNode", "type": "sqrt", "domainFrom": { "data": "nodes", "field": "weight" }, "range": [2, 18] }
  ],
  "coords": { "type": "cartesian" },
  "marks": [
    { "id": "links", "type": "rule", "from": "edges", "pipeline": "lineAA@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x":  { "scale": "gx", "field": "src.fx", "lookup": { "on": "src", "from": "sim", "key": "id" } },
        "y":  { "scale": "gy", "field": "src.fy", "lookup": { "on": "src", "from": "sim", "key": "id" } },
        "x2": { "scale": "gx", "field": "dst.fx", "lookup": { "on": "dst", "from": "sim", "key": "id" } },
        "y2": { "scale": "gy", "field": "dst.fy", "lookup": { "on": "dst", "from": "sim", "key": "id" } },
        "strokeWidth": { "field": "weight", "scale": { "type": "linear", "range": [0.5, 3] } },
        "color": { "value": "#55607a", "opacity": 0.5 }
      } },
    { "id": "verts", "type": "point", "from": "sim", "pipeline": "points@1",
      "encoding": {
        "x":    { "scale": "gx", "field": "fx" },
        "y":    { "scale": "gy", "field": "fy" },
        "size": { "scale": "rNode", "field": "weight" },
        "color":{ "value": "#8ab4f8" }
      } }
  ],
  "layers": [ { "id": "main", "region": { "x":[0,1], "y":[0,1] }, "marks": ["links","verts"] } ],
  "interaction": {
    "panZoom": { "x": { "scale": "gx", "mode": "translateScale" }, "y": { "scale": "gy", "mode": "translateScale" } },
    "drag": { "target": "verts", "writes": ["sim.fx","sim.fy"], "pin": true, "reheat": 0.3 }
  }
}
```

This example exercises every hard feature: a stateful per-frame `iterative` transform with engine-owned persistent state (`state:"persistent"`), a relational `lookup` so the edge mark resolves endpoint positions from the `sim` table by `id`, a foreign-key `ref` typing constraint on `edges.src/dst → nodes.id`, drag-interaction that writes back into transform state with reheat, and the `customCompute`/WGSL escape hatch for the inner physics.

---

## 3. Composition & typing — why the AI can't emit nonsense

The manifest is a **typed, acyclic dataflow graph over one id namespace**. Four checks reject malformed specs *before any data flows*:

1. **Reference resolution.** Every `from`/`in`/`scale`/`lookup.from` is a string into the union of `data.sources[].id ∪ transforms[].id ∪ scales[].id`. A dangling reference is a compile error. (Vega-Lite does the same for named datasets; we extend it to scales and transform outputs uniformly.)
2. **Column-set inference (the schema propagation).** Each dataset has a statically inferable column set with dtypes: a source's columns come from its `columns` map; a transform's output columns = `in`'s columns minus dropped fields plus the transform's `as`/`aggregate.as`/`formula.as` outputs. So `"field": "sma20"` on the line mark is valid only because the `window` transform declared `as:"sma20"`. A channel referencing a non-existent or wrong-dtype column fails at compile.
3. **Channel↔scale↔dtype compatibility matrix.** A channel binds `scale(field)` only if (a) the field's dtype is in the scale type's accepted-input set (`band/ordinal` ⇐ str/ordinal; `log` ⇐ positive quantitative; `time` ⇐ f64 time), and (b) the channel is in the mark type's legal channel set, and (c) the mark type is legal for the bound pipeline, and (d) the resolved channel set covers the pipeline's required vertex/instance fields (`instancedCandle@1` requires x,yOpen,yClose,yHigh,yLow; `points@1` requires x,y). This last clause is unique to a GPU target — it replaces Vega-Lite's "any mark works anywhere" with a hard pipeline-format contract mirroring `CommandProcessor::validateDrawItem`.
4. **DAG acyclicity + streaming-class coherence.** Transforms topologically sort (no cycles, no forward refs). The compiler also derives each scale's and mark's effective streaming class from its inputs and flags contradictions (e.g. a `globalRecompute` treemap feeding a mark declared `perFrame` is downgraded to the slower cadence, surfaced as a warning).

The net effect: the AI is synthesizing **a program in a strongly-typed total DSL with no general iteration** (iteration is confined to named transforms / the WGSL escape hatch), which is the regime where program-synthesis-against-a-grammar is most tractable.

---

## 4. AI-authorability assessment

### Why this is tractable
- **Constrained search space.** The grammar has a finite mark vocabulary (~7), a finite scale vocabulary (~13), and a finite-but-extensible transform vocabulary (~15 named + 1 escape hatch). The AI picks from enumerable choices and fills typed slots — closer to "fill a Vega-Lite spec" (which current models already do well) than open-ended code generation. The PRIOR-ART convergence (Vega ~40 transforms, ggplot2 ~45 geoms, all reducing to the same ~9 marks / ~13 scales) means the target vocabulary is *stable and well-represented in pretraining*.
- **Compiler-in-the-loop = verifiable synthesis.** Every check in §3 runs without data, so the AI gets a precise, localized error ("scale `yp` type `log` rejects field `close` which can be ≤0") and can repair. This is the classic execution-guided / repair loop that makes DSL synthesis converge.

### What the model needs in context
1. **The grammar card**: the enumerated mark/scale/transform vocabularies with each one's required/optional channels and accepted dtypes, plus the pipeline→mark→required-format table (derived from `PipelineCatalog.cpp` + `Geometry.hpp`).
2. **A feed schema descriptor**: the available `streamKey`s and `field` names/dtypes/roles for the target feed (so it knows `field:close` exists and is f32, time is f64 — and that **f64 time must stay on CPU** because WebGPU has no f64; epoch-ms overflows f32 mantissa per GPU-COMPUTE).
3. **The streaming-class table**: which transforms are incremental vs windowed vs globalRecompute vs ill-defined-under-streaming, so it sets cadences sensibly and never declares a `percentOfWhole`/`globalNormalize` without a baseline policy (STREAMING class-4).
4. **A handful of worked manifests** (the three above) as few-shot anchors.

### Failure modes & mitigations
| Failure mode | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Dangling/typo references | §3.1 resolution check → repair loop |
| Wrong scale for dtype (log on signed perf) | §3.3 matrix → error; diverging/symlog suggested |
| Channel set doesn't cover pipeline format | §3.3 clause (d) → error names the missing channel |
| Mis-set streaming cadence (treemap perFrame) | §4 coherence pass downgrades + warns |
| Ill-defined-under-stream (percent-of-whole) | linter requires explicit `baseline` policy or rejects |
| Reaches for escape hatch when a named transform exists | static analysis: if a `customCompute` IO signature matches a named transform, suggest it |
| Hallucinated WGSL in escape hatch | WGSL is Tint-validated at compile (Dawn already links Tint); IO bindings checked against declared read/readWrite columns; sandboxed (no host calls) |
| Unbounded retention → OOM | every stream source must declare `retention`; default `keepLast` enforced |

### Making manifests verifiable: test one manifest against many feeds
The decisive verification asset is a **manifest test harness**: a manifest is a pure function `feed → frames`, so we replay it against a *corpus of synthetic feeds* and assert invariants without a human or a GPU:
- **Property invariants** (feed-independent): every emitted instance's channels are finite; rect `x0≤x1, y0≤y1`; all positions land in the pane region after scale application; instance/vertex counts match the pipeline's required format stride; no NaN/Inf reaches a buffer.
- **Domain invariants**: after N appended records, each auto-domained scale's domain contains all bound field values (streaming `extend` correctness).
- **Differential / golden**: run the same manifest through a reference CPU evaluator and the engine; assert pixel-or-buffer parity (DynaCharting already has Dawn-golden parity tests — extend them to manifest-emitted geometry).
- **Adversarial feeds**: empty feed, single record, monotonic, all-equal (degenerate domain → scale must not divide-by-zero), out-of-order `t`, NaN value, burst of 10⁶ records (retention + budget). A manifest that survives the corpus is certified; the harness is the unit test the AI's output is graded against — closing the synthesis loop.

